>>69040401
I feel it all the time. Then I pick up the pen and draw anyway.

Art isn’t about motivation, it’s about discipline. Even if you don’t study but just challenge yourself with fun images you’ll grow. Slower than if you study, sure. But as long as you’re drawing with the mindset of getting better, I think it’ll happen. Motivation is fleeting, but habits and discipline are strong.

It is also okay to take a break. Please do, even if it’s for mental or for physical. Don’t push through pain like I do, and end up spending every night suffering.

>>69040679
It is very hard to learn to let go and accept something as flawed. I still struggle with this, but I find most of the time only I notice those flaws. Traditional does force you to learn to accept errors and that you can’t always rework something forever,
